<p class="hcp3">Step 2 of 6:</p>
<p class="hcp3">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="hcp4">Now that you have 
 created a blank slate to work on, you can begin modeling the events in 
 your scenario and the causal dependencies between the events. &nbsp;First, 
 let’s create the event we are most concerned with: the event that Tony 
 commits murder.</p>
<p class="hcp4">Click on the “<a title="Click here to view the screen shot." href="New_Event.htm" id="a3" target="_blank" class="hcp5">Add Event</a>” <img src="../image78.gif"
													style="border: none;
															width: 21px;
															height: 21px;
															border-style: none;
															border-style: none;"
													width=21
													height=21
													border="0"> &nbsp;Button 
 in the Model Toolbar, and click on the location within the Layout Editor 
 frame where you would like to place the event. &nbsp;A 
 box with an undefined label should appear. &nbsp;To 
 name this event, right click on it and select “Edit Event” from the popup 
 menu. &nbsp;The 
 Event Editor dialog box will then come up. &nbsp;In 
 the “General” tab, you can specify the name of the event, and the object 
 to which it applies. &nbsp;In 
 this case, the event will be “Commit Murder” and the object to which it 
 applies will be “Tony Soprano.”</p>
<p class="hcp4">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="hcp4">The third field in 
 that tab, “Leak Probability” is the probability the event will occur due 
 to all other unmodeled causes. &nbsp;In 
 this case, we will leave it at 0.</p>
<p class="hcp4">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="hcp4"><span style="font-weight: normal;">Now, 
 we should consider what would cause Tony to commit murder. &nbsp;As 
 most detectives might tell you, a crime requires motive and opportunity. 
 &nbsp;In the 
 situation on The Sopranos, the motivation was Salvatore being caught wearing 
 a wire for the FBI. &nbsp;The 
 opportunity for the murder came when Tony and Salvatore took a boat ride 
 together. &nbsp;</span></p>
<p class="hcp4">&nbsp;</p>
<p class="hcp4">Let’s add these events 
 to the model. &nbsp;Again 
 click on the New Event button, and add the events “Caught wearing wire” 
 applied to “Salvatore Bonpensier” and “Boat ride” applied to “Tony and 
 Salvatore.”</p>
<p class="hcp4">&nbsp;</p>
